  "target_response": {
    "text": "Probably not broken — 7.5 hours is a solid duration, and feeling wrecked on waking is very often plain sleep inertia, especially if you woke out of deep sleep or your schedule has shifted lately. Since your sleep is manually logged and I don't have recovery, heart-rate, or baseline data, I can't check quality signals, so go by how the grogginess behaves: if it lifts within the first hour of moving around, light, and breakfast, it's the normal kind. Keep your wake time consistent and get morning light soon after waking — those two do more for morning grogginess than almost anything else. One distinction worth knowing: grogginess that fades is benign, while waking gasping or choking, or crushing daytime sleepiness that never lifts, is worth raising with a doctor.",
